Package io.atlasmap.core

Class ADMArchiveHandler

java.lang.Object
io.atlasmap.core.ADMArchiveHandler
public class ADMArchiveHandler extends Object
The API for handling ADM archive. It encapsulates ADM archive structure and format and isolate file/stream I/O and serialization/deserializatiopn from other part. ADM archive is a zipped archive file or its exploded directory which contains
  • Mapping Definition file (atlasmapping-UI.n.json)
  • Document Catalog file (document-catalog.json
  • Document specification files (e.g. specification/SOURCE/some-json-doc-id/0)
  • Document inspection result files (e.g. inspected/SOURCE/some-json-doc-id/inspected.json)
  • Java libraries (jar files in lib/ directory)
In addition to above, older version of ADM archive has a gzipped digest file ADMDigest which contains all document metadata and mapping definition in a single JSON file (adm-catalog-files-n.gz). The digest file is deprecated and newer version of AtlasMap converts it into Document catalog file and Document specifications automatically.
load(Path) export(OutputStream)
Note that at this moment Java library directory is not managed by this class. Only when it imports/exports ADM archive file, library jars are extracted/bundled if isIgnoreLibrary() is set to false.

    • deleteDocument

      public void deleteDocument(DataSourceType dsType, String documentId) throws AtlasException
      Deletes the Document specification, inspection result and metadata from the DocumentCatalog. This also invokes AtlasMappingHandler.removeDocumentReference(DocumentKey) to remove all the Document references from the Mapping Definition.
      Parameters:
      dsType - SOURCE or TARGET
      documentId - Document ID of the Document to be deleted
      Throws:
      AtlasException
